  "text": "Mutants were made of 9 of the 11 loci linked to the identified promoters. Two of the in vivo-induced genes, entC and iucB, have been studied in vivo previously [CITATION_1] and were excluded from further analysis. Mutants at the nine other loci were tested in competition with the wild type in the mouse peritonitis model. In these infections, the only mutant showing attenuation was CFT073 degS.",
